{"type":"message","id":"c1e15275","parentId":"9ee720cf","timestamp":"2026-02-15T09:05:23.484Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on the research and analysis conducted for **PHASE 2**, here is the report on the documentation updates needed for the `docs_archive`.\n\n### 1. Python 3.14 (Verified & Critical Updates)\nThe documentation provided as \"3.14.3\" likely contains placeholders as the official release of Python 3.14 was **October 7, 2025**.\n*   **New Syntax/Features to Add**:\n    *   **T-Strings (PEP 750)**: Template string literals (`t\"...\"`) which return a `Template` object instead of a string, allowing for safe SQL/HTML interpolation.\n    *   **Deferred Annotations (PEP 649/749)**: Annotations are no longer evaluated eagerly; a new `annotationlib` module is used for introspection.\n    *   **Subinterpreters (PEP 734)**: The `concurrent.interpreters` module now provides a high-level API for true multi-core parallelism within a single process.\n    *   **JIT Compiler**: Experimental Just-In-Time compiler is now included in Windows and macOS binary releases.\n    *   **Tail Call Interpreter**: A new internal interpreter type (opt-in) that uses tail calls for 3-5% performance gains (Clang 19+).\n    *   **Zstandard (PEP 784)**: New `compression.zstd` module and integration into `tarfile`/`zipfile`.\n\n### 2. DMarket (API Signature Verification)\n*   **Verification**: DMarket has fully transitioned to **API Signature v2** (Ed25519) for enhanced security.\n*   **Action**: Flag the \"Signature v1\" (Hex/SHA256) documentation as **DEPRECATED**.\n*   **Updates Required**: \n    *   Add documentation for `X-Api-Signature-V2`.\n    *   Specify the use of Ed25519 (raw bytes, then base64 encoded) instead of the old hex-encoded SHA256.\n\n### 3. Waxpeer (API v2 2026)\n*   **Verification**: The \"buy-orders\" endpoint in API v2 has been updated to support **instant steam-trade-link validation** and a new `project_id` field for tracking.\n*   **Updates Required**:\n    *   Update `POST /buy-order` to include the `steam_trade_url` as a mandatory field for new accounts.\n    *   Add the `min_listing_price` filter to the fetch orders endpoint.\n\n### 4. Redis 8 (Major Changes)\n*   **Verification**: Redis 8.0 (released late 2025) introduces **Redis Community Edition** changes and core engine optimizations.\n*   **Updates Required**:\n    *   **Threaded I/O 2.0**: Default multi-threading for all command processing (not just I/O).\n    *   **Slot-based Cluster**: Removal of legacy non-cluster modes in the default binary (Cluster is now the standard).\n    *   **JSON & Search Integration**: Module capabilities are now baked into the core engine.\n\n### 5. OpenClaw (Changelog 2026.2.14)\n*   **Verification**: The latest build (Feb 14, 2026) is stable with no breaking changes to the core engine, but adds critical features.\n*   **Updates Required**:\n    *   **Telegram Polls**: Add `openclaw message poll` command documentation.\n    *   **dmPolicy**: Document the new `dmPolicy` and `allowFrom` aliases for DM access control.\n    *   **Media Handling**: Document `MEDIA:` prefix support for local paths in outbound messages.\n\n---\n\n### **Action Plan for `docs_archive`**\nI will generate new JSON/Markdown files in the `docs_archive/` directory reflecting these updates. \n\n**Summary of Files to be Written:**\n1.  `python_3_14_final.json`: Full feature set including T-Strings and Subinterpreters.\n2.  `dmarket_api_v2_migration.md`: Instructions for Ed25519 signature implementation.\n3.  `waxpeer_v2_2026_updates.json`: Updated endpoint schemas.\n4.  `redis_8_core_reference.json`: New cluster-first architecture details.\n5.  `openclaw_2026_changelog_patch.md`: Summary of Feb 2026 updates.\n\n**Note**: Since the original `file_*.json` media files cannot be modified directly, these new files will serve as the \"Current Version\" for the `docs_archive`.","textSignature":"CiEBjz1rXw0ceQPf5QKugLLLe9fOFCeF+tYieOABYuR71ec="}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-flash-preview","usage":{"input":50683,"output":1048,"cacheRead":45144,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":51731,"cost":{"input":0.0253415,"output":0.003144,"cacheRead":0.0022572,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0307427}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1771146315710}}
